Teams should:

- Start by identifying the editing model, not the component
- Use one of the three enterprise editing models wherever possible
- Match the weight of the experience to the complexity and risk of the task
- Keep platform implementations aligned to the same underlying model

Teams should not:

- Create new editing models without a compelling reason
- Use in-context editing for high-risk or highly dependent tasks
- Use focused-in-context patterns as a substitute for journeys that should be dedicated screens
- Diverge solely because of platform convention

Exceptions should be documented and discussed with GEL.
